<p>I am making a Sinatra App inside a container, But whenever I want to see the changes I have to detach and run:</p>  <p><code>docker restart &lt;container_ID&gt;</code></p>  <p>to see the changes.</p>  <p>Is there any way that I could restart the docker from within to see the changes?</p>  <p>I cloned <a href="https://github.com/tcnksm-sample/docker-sinatra.git" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/tcnksm-sample/docker-sinatra.git</a> </p>  <p>Build <code>sudo docker build -t sinatra .</code></p>  <p>Run container <code>sudo docker run -d -p 4567:4567 sinatra</code></p>  <p>Enter the container terminal <code>sudo docker exec -it &lt;container_ID&gt; bash</code></p>  <p>Changed the app.rb file but nothing changed on <a href="http://localhost:4567" rel="nofollow">http://localhost:4567</a>, So I detach from the container and ran <code>docker restart &lt;container_ID&gt;</code> to see the changes. Since I am going to change the app.rb alot It is so inconvenient for every time I change something I have to detach and run <code>docker restart &lt;container_ID&gt;</code></p>